Subject: SBIePay 2.0 | NEFT / RTGS / MIS — End-to-End Message Flow Diagram (DEV)

Dear Team,

Please find attached the end-to-end message flow diagram for the NEFT / RTGS / MIS integration between IBM MQ and Kafka on the DEV environment.

The diagram covers the complete transaction lifecycle in two legs:

Leg 1 - Dealer Validation (steps 1-11)
Challan generated on SBIePay 2.0 with ATRN, request posted by IPH to NeftInboundQueue, picked up by the neft-mq-source connector and published to neft.inbound.kafka.topic. The application consumes, validates (VAN, amount, date, duplicate) and publishes the response to neft.outbound.kafka.topic, which the neft-mq-sink connector delivers back to NeftOutBoundQueue as the ACK to IPH.

Leg 2 - MIS (steps 12-21)
MIS is generated by IPH only on a successful Y|NA acknowledgement. On an N response the flow stops and no MIS is raised. The MIS request follows the same path via NeftMISCInboundQueue and the mis-mq-source / mis-mq-sink connector pair, concluding with the IPH audit moving from Pending CorpMisAck to MIS Received Ack and the transaction being marked successful.

The RTGS flow is identical, using queue manager SBI_RTGS on port 2005 and the corresponding rtgs.* topics.

Environment details, the connector inventory and the colour legend are included on the right-hand side of the diagram for reference. The MQ connectivity and Kafka platform details are as currently configured in the dev-kafka namespace.

